<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,2001,2026]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1436,151,501]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="594" pageId="0" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,212,2001,2026]" pageId="0" pageNumber="593">Male</emphasis>
Body small, medium size for the tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[692,858,2001,2026]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Meconematini">Meconematini</taxonomicName>
. Fastigium frontis moderately inclined, fastigium verticis conical, apex obtusely rounded with a longitudinal sulcus on disc. Eyes oval, prominent anteriorly and externally. Apical segment of maxillary palpi longer than subapical one, apex slightly swollen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594">Pronotum short, anterior and median transversal sulci indistinct, posterior transversal sulcus distinct; anterior margin moderately straight, posterior margin obtusely rounded; lateral lobe of pronotum long and high equal; humeral sinus shallow. Thoracic auditory spiracle comparatively large, oval.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594">
All femora without spines on ventral surface. Forecoxa with a spine, foretibiae with 
<number box="[1157,1171,332,357]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594" value="5.0">5</number>
long spines and 
<number box="[1364,1378,332,357]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594" value="6.0">6</number>
long spines on inner and outer sides of ventral surface separately (including one pair of apical spines); tibial tympana open on both sides, elliptical. Mesotibiae with 
<number box="[676,690,404,429]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594" value="5.0">5</number>
long spines and 
<number box="[879,893,404,429]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594" value="6.0">6</number>
long spines on internal side and external side of ventral surface separately. Posttibiae with 
<number box="[647,717,439,464]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594" value="27.5" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="26.0">26–29</number>
spines on inner and outer sides of dorsal surface separately, bearing one pair of dorsal apical spurs and two pairs of ventral apical spurs.
</paragraph>
