<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="595" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1184]" pageId="2" pageNumber="595">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1052,1077]" pageId="2" pageNumber="595">Discussion.</emphasis>
The new species differs from the known species of the genus in: male cerci with basal area robust, cylindrical; apical half depressed, tumid dorsally, curved dorso-caudally, apices rounded; tenth abdominal tergite with a pair of long posterior processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1132,1159,1184]" pageId="2" pageNumber="595" type="etymology">
